rComments: Classic Humanities professor. Get ready to read a textbook for homework and show up for participation marks kind of class. Plenty of reading and writing, grading is ok but not generous.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Participation matters', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: I found her a little too unorthodox and lofty. Plus, her grading criteria were simply off the charts crazy.

Baffled by the negative comments! Arrive ready to work, engaged, and with a willingness to do the readings and she will be your number-one cheerleader. Just a lovely, fun, enthusiastic, and supes supportive person ;). If she were to use any idea or work of mine it would be an honour. Take her class and rejoice in your fortune!
Arrogant, self absorbed prof. Very confusing and speaks only about HER research, nothing else being done by other's ideas, studies, etc.  extremely RUDE and abrasive
can seem really abrasive in emails, but don't let that scare you off - lively and thoughtful and supportive in person.

Enthusiastic, funny, organised, and extremely bright. Can seem a bit stand-offish, but usually that's just because she's insanely busy; if you need help, ask for it, and she'll be on your side. Doesn't really use handouts, though; take lots of notes.
the worst prof ever, you can only respect someone that respects you

I had her for both lin256 & lin356. She has high expectations but she's a good prof. Her classes aren't easy. Lin256 was definitely the better course. Saying "she swipes research from her students" is stupid so whoever said that below me needs to learn to respect profs. You can be frustrated but don't run your mouth like that. It's rude.

The class moved at a constant pace. The grading was very hard and the tests you had to study for for a damn while, but overall the material was very interesting. I can understand why some would see her as arrogant. She supplies you the raw material, but you really need to jump into the subject matter entirely to get ahead.
course itself is interesting, her lectures are well conducted but tests/projects are quite challengeable. Workload is heavy and her office hours are helpless.

Overall very nice, great prof!  Granted the tests are not mere regurgitation of information but if you study you can do well.  The course material is very interesting and she is passionate about it and a good speaker!
Very high expectations, and large workload

By far the most arrogant professor I've ever had, as well as extremely vague in lectures, assignments, and marking.  She prattles on about how she lived in Britain for twenty minutes, swipes research from students, and wears bizarre, expensive-looking fanny packs.  Sum: "I swear I have a career!"

*shudder*  Rude, arrogant as all hell, this prof is my worst nightmare. Doesn't tell you how to do anything that's on the test or the assignment. The worst part of the project is trying to figure out WHAT SHE WANTS. **** **** ****
she is passionate about her work, but definitely not passionate about teaching or her students.
hated the class with a passion- glad to get out of it with my GPA intact.  very demanding.

She is a very energetic professor who knows what she is talking about. She tries to make the students think when writing the tests instead of purely regurgitating the information they learned in text books and lectures. She is an okay prof.
Lots of materials weren't mentioned at all in class but she expects us to know them for the test! And she was really unhelpful in clarifying concepts.
Forget that she's almost impossible to please -- she uses her student's work in her books.  I don't recall seeing any credit assigned to any name other than hers!
Horrible class
She is an awesome prof. She really enjoys her work and takes it serious. Show up, do your work, an easy 80 will come your way.
This class was AWFUL!
Be prepared to work and your efforts will be rewarded.
don't bother taking this class.
demanding material, tough marker, but her class is worth the effort.
